description:
Feedzai is the world's first RiskOps platform, and market leader in safeguarding global commerce with today's most advanced cloud-based risk management platform, powered by machine learning and artificial intelligence. Feedzai is securing the transition to a cashless world while enabling digital trust in every transaction and payment type. The world's largest banks, processors, and retailers trust Feedzai to protect trillions of dollars and manage risk while improving the customer experience for everyday users, without compromising privacy. Feedzai is a Series D company and has raised $282M to date with a current valuation of $1.5B. Its technology protects 800 million people in 190 countries.
The
Data Science Team
within Customer Success is highly engaged with our clients making use of their critical thinking skills with a business-focused mentality and customer-facing attitude. They activate, maintain, and support clients, develop models and rules, and train & enable them. In addition, they work cross-functionally with other departments (e.g., Research, Product, Marketing) in a collaborative team spirit spanning the globe to ensure we deliver best in class risk prevention solutions. Being on the frontline of fighting crime and protecting people from financial harm is incredibly inspiring to each of us.
Join Us!
Your Day to Day:
Understanding the data which our clients provide to us;
Cleaning that data and validating that it is correct;
Preprocessing the data, usually by using a mixture of shell scripts and a programming language such as Python, Java, Scala, etc
Iteratively computing features and tuning parameters to improve the quality of the model;
Communicating your findings to the project manager and assisting him/her in decision making on the Data Science part of the project;
Work together with key stakeholders (data scientists, engineers, risk managers) from our clients;
Work with other parts of the organization (Product, Research, etc.) to improve processes, best practices and tooling.
You Have & You Know-how:
MSc or PhD in Computer Science, Electrical Engineering, Statistics, Applied Mathematics, Physics or related field;
Proficient in Machine Learning (training and testing, avoiding overfit, etc.);
Knowledge of Big Data technologies such as Spark, Hadoop and related;
Proficiency in bash, Python and either Java or Scala;
Knowledge of resource monitoring and runtime optimization (both at JVM and OS level);
Knowledge of statistics or data visualization is a plus;
Knowledge of tree based algorithms (Random Forests, XGBoost, LGBM) is a plus;
Knowledge of Deep Learning algorithms is a plus;
Ability to communicate your findings in a clear way.
As a federal contractor, Feedzai requires all US-based employees to be vaccinated against COVID-19 and provide proof of such a vaccine upon employment, unless you need a reasonable accommodation authorized by federal, state, or local law. By applying to this role, you acknowledge that you understand this requirement and are willing to comply with our policy should an offer of employment be made.
The Customer Success Team
is responsible for delivering our product to our clients. This includes education, configuration, solution development, and risk strategy to enable our clients to address their pain points. We collaborate with our clients to ensure they have the right solution, build out a strategy and training plan for them, and then support them through each phase of our client lifecycle. We grow at a fast clip and believe no challenge is too big or too small. Therefore, we have an open environment that encourages us to lean in, try new things, and discover our potential.
Join Us!
#LI-IP1 #LI-remote
Your First 30-Days at Feedzai:
You will be immersed in our brand with training, connections, and one-on-one time with your manager. You may shadow your colleagues virtually or onsite at an office depending on where you work as you are supported through your Feedzai journey. In addition, you will have access to a ton of information to give you history, context, and all the knowledge you can handle about Feedzai and the team. Finally, you will start working on projects and collaborating on work currently being done. We can't wait to have you join the team!
Life at Feedzai Instagram
Feedzai Culture
Feedzai is an Equal Opportunity Employer and we value diversity at our company. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, or disability status.
Feedzai does not accept unsolicited resumes from recruiters or employment agencies.

Techstars seeks an experienced Data Scientist to join a growing team of investment professionals shaping our fund and investment strategy in support of ambitious entrepreneurs worldwide. As an integral member of the Techstars Capital team, the Data Scientist will be responsible for owning and delivering a suite of data and analytics solutions to support the firm's capital formation, investment strategy, fund management, and investor relations activities globally. We are searching for a person who is an excellent problem solver and analytical thinker, is highly technical and a skilled insights specialist, is a proven leader who can develop and execute against a roadmap, wants to build new data tools and products that contribute to investment decision-making on a global scale, is excited about working as part of a broader team, and is passionate about venture capital and high-growth entrepreneurship.
Duties and Responsibilities
Collect, clean, aggregate, analyze, and visualize structured and unstructured datasets from a variety of public and private sources;
Develop and maintain quantitative/statistical/machine learning models, databases, dashboards, tools, and performance metrics;
Produce actionable insights (data + story) in support of the firm's capital formation, investment strategy, fund management, and investor relations activities globally
Design and implement procedures that ensure best-in-class data generation, stewardship, pipelines, and workflows;
Work seamlessly in an interdisciplinary team of professionals on the Capital team; collaborate with key partners across the business (Accelerator Investments, Engineering, Portfolio Services, Finance, Legal, Executive);
Lead and support various thought-leadership initiatives on the Capital team and throughout the organization, and develop and maintain new tools for reporting and insights
Mentor and lead junior staff
Qualifications
5+ years of work experience in a quantitative research role, with demonstrated love of data analytics, an intellectual curiosity, a desire to constantly learn and grow;
Proficiency in programming languages for data and statistical analysis (R, Python), databases (SQL, APIs), infrastructure (AWS), and data visualization (Tableau, D3, Shiny);
Demonstrated ability to independently build predictive/machine learning models and produce data-driven insights for business and/or investment audiences;
Experience and interest in building data products, processes, and dashboards; leading teams in the production of such outputs a plus
Domain knowledge and interest in entrepreneurship, venture capital, and technology;
Work experience in venture capital, private equity, or investment banking is a plus;
Knowledge of existing data sources in startups and venture capital (PitchBook, Crunchbase, Burgiss, Prequin) is a plus;
The ability to work both independently and within a team; possess a congenial disposition, an entrepreneurial spirit, and have comfort in an informal work environment; and
A conviction that entrepreneurs create a better future and a desire to support our mission to help entrepreneurs succeed.
Compensation range:
$125,000 - $175,000 + 10% Bonus
US Benefits
About Techstars
Techstars is the worldwide network that helps entrepreneurs succeed. Founded in 2006, Techstars began with three simple ideas - entrepreneurs create a better future for everyone, collaboration drives innovation and great ideas can come from anywhere. Now we are on a mission to enable every person on the planet to contribute to, and benefit from, the success of entrepreneurs. In addition to operating accelerator programs and venture capital funds, we do this by connecting startups, investors, corporations and cities to help build thriving startup communities. Techstars has invested in more than 2,300 companies with a combined market cap of more than $29B.
Techstars' mission is to help entrepreneurs succeed wherever they are in the world and whatever their background is. Regional accelerator programs all around the world are the cornerstone of the strategy. The investment approach is fundamentally driven by the worldwide network of managing directors, who interact with startup founders daily, guiding, mentoring and cultivating them along the journey. The scale of this reach results in a diversified strategy that provides investors with a uniquely qualified deal flow.
We help Techstars founders connect with other entrepreneurs, experts, mentors, alumni, investors, community leaders, and corporations to grow their companies.
www.techstars.com

Contractors
Currently, all staff and non-staff are working remotely except for select roles that have an in office requirement. We value the health and safety of the people that work for us above all else, and our office re-openings will remain contingent on the course of the COVID variants and federal, state and local safety guidelines and recommendations.
DATA SCIENTIST
A&E Television Networks, LLC seeks a Data Scientist in New York, New York. Telecommuting/working from home is permissible. Responsible for building and maintaining large-scale cloud-based Data Science forecasting models with Nielsen AMRLD and STB audience data, audience engagement data (social, web, email, mobile, etc.), and other consumer data. Specific duties include:
Executing the full-scope of advanced analytic techniques on audience viewership and other engagement data with the objectives of creating inferences, predictions, and prescriptive recommendations for improvements to business processes, and the metrics to monitor those improvements;
Defining data science opportunities that will push our linear and digital opportunities forward, utilizing a strong command of techniques and algorithms necessary to build sophisticated predictive Data Science models, as well as a demonstrated practical ability to determine where to invest time, synthesize actionable findings across diverse assignments, and present these findings to an audience with varying levels of background in analytics;
Partnering closely with a team of business analysts and data engineers leading our strategy to build and implementation of machine learning models for predictive and prescriptive analytics, including recommendation engines;
Designing, building, training, and maintaining data science models for predictive and prescriptive advanced audience viewership data to satisfy Use Cases for the business;
Planning and leading the execution of the data science analytics life-cycle, leveraging significant experience in leading this type of work in previous roles; surveying varied data sources in relational databases, Hadoop, flat files, and external sources for analytic relevance;
Performing data survey, profile screening, pre-processing, and modelling data management for validation (e.g. holdout, cross-validation); designing Python/R/SQL queries to parse and extract data as needed, and present findings in Tableau and D3;
Executing algorithms' selection to interpret results for both causal inferences and predictive effectiveness;
Synthesizing appropriate recommendations for action and changes, and presenting findings in PPT, Tableau and D3, to suggest actions and changes to a broad audience while managing follow-ups and execution; and
Building programs to educate stakeholders as to how best to leverage and engage data resources, helping us become a more data-driven organization.
YOUR STORY:
Must have a Bachelor’s degree, or foreign equivalent, in Computer Science or related field, plus five (5) years of experience in job offered or in a related data analysis and/or development role.
Must have experience with each of the followings:
Hands-on knowledge of media data and all phases in building and maintaining largescale cloud-based Data Science forecasting models with Nielsen AMRLD and STB audience data, audience engagement data (social, web, email, and mobile), and other consumer data.
Media data experience wrangling, analyzing, and normalizing data, and building databases in S3 using Python/SQL.
Writing queries on large and complex data sets for immediate analysis.
Demonstrable experience with Machine Learning and other data science processes (e.g. Linear Regression models, Random Forrest models, and GBM/xgboost models).
Experience with and ability to work with data including rapid prototyping and coding skills using common data scientists tools.
Knowledge of advanced statistical method, pattern recognition and outlier detection algorithms, and predictive modeling methods

